Package: rustyfilters
Title: Fast Focal and Speckle Filters for Matrices and Arrays
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Hugh", "Graham", , "hugh@belian.earth", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Minimal, high-performance moving-window filters for numeric
    matrices, 3-D arrays and, optionally, 'terra' SpatRaster and
    'gdalraster' GDALRaster objects. Provides SAR speckle filters (Lee,
    enhanced Lee, Lee sigma classic and improved, Frost, Kuan, Gamma-MAP),
    smoothing and edge-preserving filters (mean, Gaussian, median,
    bilateral, guided), focal statistics (min, max, range, standard
    deviation, sum, mode) and kernel convolution (including Sobel and
    Laplacian), each with an NA-aware default and a documented fast path,
    multi-threaded via 'Rust' and 'rayon'.
License: Apache License (>= 2)
URL: https://github.com/belian-earth/rustyfilters, https://belian-earth.github.io/rustyfilters/
BugReports: https://github.com/belian-earth/rustyfilters/issues
